1. Explain the importance of Test Pyramid.
The Test Pyramid defines the ideal distribution of tests.
It recommends more unit tests, fewer UI tests.
Helps in early defect detection.
Reduces execution time and maintenance cost.
Improves overall quality and test reliability.

2. Which Agile Quadrant is suitable for Manual Testing? Why?
Agile Quadrant Q2 is suitable for manual testing.
It focuses on business-facing tests.
Includes exploratory, usability, and acceptance testing.
Manual testing is needed for user behavior validation.
Human judgment is critical in this quadrant.

3. Which Test Pyramid layer is easier to test and detects bugs early? Explain.
Unit testing layer is easiest to test.
It tests individual methods or functions in isolation.
Execution is fast and simple to automate.
Bugs are found during development itself.
Fixing defects here is cheapest and fastest.